mapinfo.coord_coord(lat, lon, dist, bearing)¶

Finds the lat/lon coordinates “dist” km away from the given “lat” and “lon” coordinate along the given compass “bearing”

Parameters

  • lat (float) – First point’s latitude (dd)

  • lon (float) – First point’s longitude (dd)

  • dist (float) – Distance in km the second point should be from the first point

  • bearing (float) – Bearing in degrees from the first point to the second

Return type

list

Returns

Latitude and longitude in DD of the second point

mapinfo.find_obj_coords(x, y, map_size, ULHC_lat, ULHC_lon)¶

Convert the provided object’s x/y coordinate to lat/lon

Parameters

  • x (float) – The distance of the object from the upper left hand corner of the map in the horizontal direction. x=0 means the object is on the left border of the map and x=1 means the object is on the right border

  • y (float) – The distance of the object from the upper left hand corner of the map in the vertical direction. y=0 means the object is on the top border of the map and y=1 means the object is on the bottom border

  • map_size (float) – The length/width of the map in km (all maps are square)

  • ULHC_lat (float) – The true world estimated latidude of the map’s upper left hand corner point

  • ULHC_lon (float) – The true world estimated longitude of the map’s upper left hand corner point

Return type

list

Returns

Estimated latitude and longitude of the object’s position

class acmi.ACMI(num_objs=1)¶

Class used to create and maintain a given ACMI file used by the downloadable program Tacview

Initialize class object and create a member dict named “obj_ids” to hold unique/valid HEX ID values for each object to be displayed

Parameters

num_objs (int) – Number of objects to simulaneously display in Tacview
